  "slug": "fudgy-vegan-cookies",
  "title": "Fudgy Vegan Cookies",
  "subtitle": "Crisp at the edges, soft in the middle.",
  "excerpt": "Fudgy Vegan Cookies. A baking recipe from Rebecca's collection, straightforward, reliable, worth weighing rather than scooping.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook, a recipe she's made many times in her own kitchen.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "These are fudgy vegan chocolate cookies: crisp at the edges, soft and brownie-like in the middle. Apple sauce stands in for egg and keeps them moist. The chocolate and dairy-free butter are melted together over a pan of simmering water, then folded into the whipped apple and sugar base. The batter firms up quickly at room temperature, so scoop and bake fast."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pull the cookies from the oven when the edges are set but the middles still look slightly underdone. They firm up as they cool."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
