      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "body": "See below for the optional caramel swirl.",
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Line 2 baking trays with greaseproof paper."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sieve the {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, and {{baking-powder}} into a bowl and stir to combine. Set aside."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "In a large mixing bowl, combine the {{apple-eating}} sauce, {{light-brown-sugar}}, and {{caster-sugar}}. Whip for 2 to 4 minutes with an electric hand whisk or stand mixer until smooth and pale. A wooden spoon works too, but takes longer."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Put the {{salted-butter}} and {{dark-chocolate}} into a heatproof bowl set over a pan of gently simmering water, making sure the bowl does not touch the water. Stir until fully melted and smooth. Remove from the heat."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "With the mixer on low speed, slowly pour the chocolate mixture into the apple and sugar base. Once everything is in, increase to medium speed and mix for 30 seconds."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Slowly fold in the flour mixture. The batter will look like brownie batter. Fold in the {{chocolate-chips}}."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Using a small ice cream scoop or two dessert spoons, scoop golf-ball-sized portions onto the lined trays. Leave about 7 cm between cookies as they spread. Work quickly: the batter firms up at room temperature. Bake one tray at a time in the centre of the oven."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bake for 10 minutes, then rotate the tray and bake for a further 5 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Remove from the oven. While still warm, use a circular cookie cutter slightly larger than each cookie to nudge the edges inward. This gives clean, round shapes. Press a few extra chocolate chips on top if you like."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Leave to cool on the trays for 10 to 15 minutes before moving."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Chill the dough for 30 minutes before baking. Preheat the oven properly, 180°C means 180°C on an oven thermometer, not the dial.",
              "cause": "Butter too soft, or oven not hot enough.",
              "symptom": "Cookies spread too thin and crisp"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Stop mixing as soon as the flour disappears. For chewier cookies, replace some plain flour with bread flour for more gluten.",
              "cause": "Over-mixed once the flour went in, or too much flour.",
              "symptom": "Cookies came out cakey, not chewy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Leave them on the tray for five minutes after baking. They're too soft to move when hot. Lift onto a rack with a palette knife.",
              "cause": "Tried to lift before they'd set.",
              "symptom": "Cookies stuck to the tray"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use a heavier baking tray, line with baking paper, and bake on the middle shelf.",
              "cause": "Tray too thin, or rack too low.",
              "symptom": "Burnt bottoms, raw middles"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add-ins: 75 g dark chocolate chips, chopped walnuts, dried cranberries, or a pinch of sea salt on top before baking."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Gluten-free: replace plain flour with a 1-to-1 gluten-free blend that includes xanthan gum."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best eaten the same day. Store in an airtight tin at room temperature for up to 3 days."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A classic American home recipe: generous, comforting, made for a crowd. The proportions are heartier than the British equivalent; the method is built for a Sunday afternoon."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
